Package com.camerontec.catalys.core.session

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    FIXOutSender
    Session writer interface intended to be used by SendManager for sending outbound FIX messages.
    FIXOutSenderCallback
    Interface used by clients of an AsynchronousFIXOutSender to submit write requests.
    IConnectionPoint
    This uniquely defines a point of communication with an external counter party.
    IConnectionPointConfiguration
    Interface for accessing connection point related configuration information.
    IConnectionPointMatcher
    Implementations of this interface are used to compare ConnectionPoints.
    IFixLoginContextRegistry
    Interface to be implemented by classes capable of acting as a FIX login context registry.
    IFIXMessageReader
    Interface to be implemented by implementations capable of reading IFIXMessages.
    IMessageSink
    Sink for MessageEvents.
    InputFIXChannel
    Interface to be implemented by inbound FIX channels.
    IObjectRegistryByConnectionPoint
    Simple searchable registry of (session-related) objects keyed by IConnectionPoint.
    IParty
    This represents a party capable of sending and receiving over a FIX Session.
    IProcessingCompletionManager
    Interface for classes which manage post-processing of messages to cater for out of order processing (e.g.
    ISessionCustomizer
    Classes that implement this interface can be used to customize Session behaviour.
    ISessionFactory
    All Session objects should be created here.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CompIdOnlyPartyMatcher
    This can be used to loosely match two parties looking only at the CompIds.
    ConnectionPoint
    Default implementation of IConnectionPoint.
    ConnectionPointMatchingUtils
    Utility methods to help with parties with periods within the components of the each Party.
    ConnectionPointNameParser Deprecated
    Use ConnectionPointMatchingUtils instead.
    ConnectionStatusMessage
    Special kind of message which wraps up a connection status event.
    CounterpartyDetection  
    DefaultConnectionPointMatcher
    Standard ConnectionPoint matcher.
    DefaultFastMessageInputStreamReader
    Message input stream reader for reading messages from a FastInputStream.
    DefaultFixMessageInputStreamReader
    The default message input stream reader implementation.
    DotPartyTokenizer
    This class tokenizes a .-delimited party into its CompID, SubID, and LocationID components.
    FIXMessageReaderFactory  
    FlexiblePartyMatcher
    This can be used to match two parties.
    Heartbeat
    This class provides the thread which keeps heartbeat ticking over as needed.
    LooseConnectionPointMatcher
    This implementation of IConnectionPointMatcher compares ConnectionPoints ignoring the subId's and LocationID's.
    MatchingObjectRegistryByConnectionPoint
    Simple iterative matching registry of (session-related) objects by connection point.
    MessageAssembler
    This class provides the thread which listens to an input stream and assembles IFIXMessages from the incoming bytes.
    MessageProcessingInfo
    Encapsulate various processing options for messages.
    NonBlockingOperationRepeater
    Class to repeatedly attempt a non-blocking operation until it succeeds or certain period of time passes.
    Party
    Default implementation of IParty.
    PartyLooseMatcher
    This can be used to loosely match two parties.
    PartyUtils  
    ProcessingCompletionManager
    Default IProcessingCompletionManager implementation.
    ResetMessage
    Special kind of message which signals that a sequence number reset has occurred.
    SendingTimeGenerator
    Class which generates encoded FIX sending time values.
    Session
    All FIX communication takes place through a Session object.
    SessionCustomizerBase
    Base implementation of ISessionCustomizer.
    SessionDialects
    Bean giving read access to session dialects.
    SessionFactory
    Default implementation of ISessionFactory based on IConnectionPointConfiguration.
    SessionFactory.ConfigurationReferencesAccessor
    This class is simply used to allow the SessionCommandLineProcessor to lookup the values of these references.
    SessionFastConfigurationHelper
    Applies fast configuration to a session.
    SessionIDUtils
    Helper methods to determine the id of a session based on the connection point
    SessionOverseer
    Singleton object which periodically examines the usage of all started sessions in the Catalys Server in order to tune their performance.
    SessionParties
    Encapsulates the session's party and counterparty id components which provide the defaults when values are not already set in a message.

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    FatalProtocolException
    Indicates that a unrecoverable protocol error occurred.
    GarbledMessageException
    Indicates receiving a "garbled" FIX message.
    LogonException
    Indicates that there was a problem logging on.
    NonFatalProtocolException
    Indicates that a recoverable protocol error occurred.
    ProtocolException
    Indicates that some kind of protocol error occurred.
    TagOutOfOrderException
    Indicates receiving FIX message with MsgType field not at the third position.
    TimedoutException
    Indicates that the protocol timed out waiting on something.
